about.description:
The QtWayland module consists of two parts.

Wayland platform plugin --
    Enables Qt applications to be run as Wayland clients.

QtWaylandCompositor API --
    Enables the creation of Wayland compositors using Qt and QtQuick.

name: qt6-wayland
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "6.6.0" %}
package:
  name: qt6-wayland
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://download.qt.io/official_releases/qt/{{ version.rpartition('.')[0] }}/{{ version }}/submodules/qtwayland-everywhere-src-{{ version }}.tar.xz
  sha256: 30c3d82d85d050c83370710a26d12c802199c51eba5c2726e9d6243edd03b7e8

build:
  skip: true   # [not linux]
  number: 0
  detect_binary_files_with_prefix: true
  run_exports:
    - {{ pin_subpackage('qt6-wayland', max_pin='x.x') }}

requirements:
  build:
    - perl
    - cmake
    - make
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - qt6-main {{ version }}             # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - sysroot_linux-64 2.17              # [linux]
    - {{ cdt('mesa-libgl-devel') }}      # [linux]
    - {{ cdt('mesa-libegl') }}           # [linux]
    - {{ cdt('mesa-libegl-devel') }}     # [linux]
    - {{ cdt('mesa-dri-drivers') }}      # [linux]
    - {{ cdt('libdrm-devel') }}          # [linux]
    - {{ cdt('libglvnd-glx') }}          # [linux]
    - {{ cdt('libglvnd-egl') }}          # [linux]
    - {{ cdt('libglvnd-devel') }}        # [linux]
  host:
    - qt6-main  {{ version }}
    - wayland
    - libvulkan-headers                  # [not osx]
    - libvulkan-loader                   # [not osx]
    - fontconfig
    - freetype
    - zlib
    - glib
    # The following X11 dependencies are only needed to build
    # the features
    #   XComposite EGL ......................... yes
    #   XComposite GLX ......................... yes
    # But these are being removed in qt 6, so it doesn't seem
    # worthwhile to build them for conda-forge in 2023
    # https://codereview.qt-project.org/c/qt/qtwayland/+/380604
    #
    # But.... they seem to get pulled in accidentally from qt-main
    # since qt-main is currently built with full X11 support
    # So for now, it doesn't really hurt to include them
    - libxkbcommon
    - xorg-libx11
    - xorg-libxext
    - xorg-libxrandr
    - xorg-libxcomposite
  run:
    # Ensure same version of qt6 is used
    - qt6-main  {{ version }}
    # Needs a run export?
    - xorg-libxcomposite

test:
  commands:
    {% set qt_libs = ["WaylandClient", "WaylandCompositor"] %}
    {% for each_qt_lib in qt_libs %}
    - test -d $PREFIX/include/qt6/Qt{{ each_qt_lib }}  # [unix]
    - test -f $PREFIX/lib/libQt6{{ each_qt_lib }}${SHLIB_EXT}  # [unix]
    {% endfor %}

about:
  home: http://qt-project.org
  license: LGPL-3.0-only
  license_file:
    - LICENSES/BSD-3-Clause.txt
    - LICENSES/GFDL-1.3-no-invariants-only.txt
    - LICENSES/GPL-2.0-only.txt
    - LICENSES/GPL-3.0-only.txt
    - LICENSES/LGPL-3.0-only.txt
    - LICENSES/LicenseRef-Qt-Commercial.txt
    - LICENSES/Qt-GPL-exception-1.0.txt

  summary: QtWayland module
  description: |
    The QtWayland module consists of two parts.

    Wayland platform plugin --
        Enables Qt applications to be run as Wayland clients.

    QtWaylandCompositor API --
        Enables the creation of Wayland compositors using Qt and QtQuick.
  doc_url: https://wiki.qt.io/QtWayland
  dev_url: https://github.com/qt/qtwayland/tree/5.15

extra:
  feedstock-name: qt-wayland
  recipe-maintainers:
    - hmaarrfk
    # qt-main added to help in case of any critical fixes or routine upgrades
    - conda-forge/qt-main
